obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE RENT RECOVERY ACT, 1853`
  line `A CT N O. VI OF 185 3`
  line `[ Passed on the 1 5 th April, 185 3.]`
  line `Recites transfer of Summary Suit from Judge to Collector, &c. and doubts in certain cases. Enacts:`
  line `1,2. If lands the subject of sale and under one tenure are situate in 2 Collectorates, the sale to be by`
  line `Collector in whose jurisdiction the greater part lies; and (2) doubt as to the collectorate in whic h the`
  line `lands or greater part lie, to be decided by Board of Revenue.`
  line `3, 4, 5, 6. Defines the meaning of the word “Collectorat e. ” And (4) defines in dependent d eputy to be`
  line `a Collector; and (5) who is to be deemed an independent deputy; and (6) authorizes notice of sale to be`
  line `stuck up at cutcherry of independent deputy.`
  line `7. What powers an independent deputy may exercise, and within what parts.`
  line `8. Notices to be stuck up at the Adawlut of the Zillah in which sale is to be made.`
  line `9. Gives validity to orders, sales, & c. made by improper Collector, and to insufficient notices before`
  line `this Act, unless proceedings to invalidate have been com menced.`
  line `10. Extends Act 25, 1850, and B.R. 8, 1819, s. 9, subject to modification under B.R. 7. 1832, s. 16.c.1,`
  line `and Act 25, 1850, to all sales under Act 8, 1835.`
  line `An Act relating to summary suits fo r arrears of rent, to sales of P utnee T al oo ks and other`
  line `s aleable tenures, and to sales of land in satisfaction of S ummary D ecrees for rent.`
  line `Whereas, by Regulation VIII. 1831 of the Bengal Code, the hearing and decision of S ummary`
  line `S uits or claims relating to arrears or exactions of rents were transferred from the J udges of the`
  line `Zila h or City Courts to the Collectors of L and R evenue of the several districts; a nd whereas by`
  line `Regulation VII. 1832 of the Bengal Code, the conduct of sales of Pu tn ee T al oo ks and other`
  line `saleable tenures under Regulations VIII. 18 19 and I. 1820 of the same Code, and the performance`
  line `of other acts preparatory to, or connected with, such sales were transferred of the Collecto r or`
  line `Deputy Collector, of Land R evenue, or Head Assistant to the Collector or Deputy Collector`
  line `subject to an appeal as therein provided; a nd whereas by Act VIII. 1835, the power there to fore`
  line `vested in the Judge of the D e wan ny Ada w l ut of selling land satisfaction of S ummary D ecrees for`
  line `rent was transferred to the Collectors of Land - R evenue, and it was enacted that all sales for the`
  line `recovery of arrears of rent held under clause 7, section 15, Regulation VII. 1799, should be`
  line `conducted by the Collector, his Deputy or duty authorized Assistant, and that ten days' notice`
  line `should be given of such sales by advertisement to be stuck up at the C utcherry of`
  line `the Zil l a h Court or local Ada w l u t, and that of the Collector; and whereas it is expedient that Act`
  line `XXV. 1850, and Section IX. Regulation VIII. 1819, of the Bengal Code, as modified by`
  line `Clause I, Section XVI. Regulation VII. 1832 of the same Code, and as altered by the said Act`
  line `XXV. 1850, should be extend ed to sales under Act VIII. 1835; a nd whereas doubts may be`
  line `entertained as to who ought to exercise the jurisdiction transferred by the abovementioned`
  line `Regulations and Acts, where lands situate within the z illah or other district of one Collector,`
  line `form part of an entire estate, paying revenue to the Collector of an another Zillah or district; I n`
  line `order therefore to avoid such doubts, and also to define who are the proper O fficers to exercise`
  line `such jurisdictions in cases where lands are situate in a district ass igned to an independent Deputy`
  line `Collector, and also in cases where lands held in p u tn ee, or other tenure, at one entire rent are`
  line `situate in two or more Collectorates, and to prevent any such decision or sale already made from`
  line `being held invalid, upon the gr ound of its having been made by an Officer of a wrong district; It`
  line `is enacted as follows:`
  line `I. If the lands which may be the subject of any such sale, or to the rent of which any such suit may`
  line `relate, be all situate in one C ollectorate, the Collector of such C ollectorate is the Collector to conduct the`
  line `sale, or to hear and decide the suit. If one T al oo k or tenure shall comprise lands situate in two or more`
  line `C ollectorates, or if any lands situate in two or more C ollectorates be held under one lease or engagement`
