  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  sourcePage 2
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `or at one entire rent, the Collector, in whose C ollectorate the greater part of such lands shall be situate, is`
  line `the Collector to conduct the sale of such Talook, or tenure or of such lands, and to hear and decide any`
  line `summary suit relating to arrears or exactions of rent in respect thereof.`
  line `II. If a Collector to whom application shall be made to exercise any of the powers above mentioned`
  line `shall entertain any doubt as to whether the lands or the greater part of them are situate within his`
  line `collectorate, he shall report the case for the order of the Board to which he is subordinate, and, if ordered`
  line `by such Board to proceed in the matter, such order shall be conclusive upon the question of his`
  line jurisdiction.
  line `III. The word “ Collectorate ” in this Act means the z illah or other district to which a Collector is`
  line `appointed, and no lands situate beyond the limits of such z illah or district shall be deemed to be situate`
  line `within the C ollectorate, by reason of their forming part of an estate paying revenue to the Collector`
  line thereof.
  line `IV. An independent Deputy Collector may, within his Deputy Collectorate, exercise all the powers`
  line `and jurisdictions of a Collector with which he may be entrusted, in the same manner and to the same`
  line `extent as a Collector may do within his Collectorate, and with reference to the exercise of such powers`
  line `and jurisdictions, his Deputy Collectorate shall be deemed a Collectorate, and he shall be deemed to be a`
  line `Collector within t he meaning of this Act.`
  line `V. An independent Deputy Collector is an O fficer appointed by Government to act as Deputy`
  line `Collector, independently of a Collector, whether his office is one for the receipt of revenue or not.A`
  line `Deputy Collectorate is the district within which an independent Deputy Collector is directed`
  line `by Government to act.`
  line `VI. In cases of sales by an independent Deputy C ollector, under the abovementioned Regulations or`
  line `Act, any notice thereby required to be stuck up at the Cutcherry of the Collector, may be stuck up at`
  line `the Cutcherry of the Deputy Collector.`
  line `VII. An independent Deputy Collector may exercise the powers assigned to him over any part of his`
  line `Deputy Collectorate in public C utcherry, in whatever part of his Deputy Collectorate the same may be`
  line `situate or held.`
  line `VIII. Any notice required by the abovementioned Regulations or Act to be given by advertisement to`
  line `be stuck up at the cutcherry of the Z illah Court or local Ada w l u t shall be stuck up at the Zi l la h Court or`
  line `local Ada wlu t within the jurisdiction of which the lands to be sold, or the greater portion of them, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be situate.`
  line `IX. No order, decision, or sale, made in the discharge of any of the duties aforesaid, under any of the`
  line `aforesaid Regulations, or under the aforesaid Act, before the pa ssing of this Act, shall be disputed, or`
  line `deemed invalid, upon the ground that the Collector, Deputy Collector, or other Officer making the same,`
  line `was not the Collector, Deputy Collector or Officer of the proper district; or upon the ground that the`
  line `Cutcherr y, at which notice of such sale was given, was not the Cutcherry of the proper district, unless`
  line `proceedings shall, previously to the passing of this Act, have been, commenced, for the purpose of`
  line `disputing the validity of such order, decision, or sale upon such ground.`
  line `X. Act XXV. 1850, and Section IX. Regulation VIII, 1819 of the Bengal Code, as modified by`
  line `Clause I, Section XVI. Regulation VII. 1832 of the same Code, except so far as the same has been altered`
  line `by the said Act XXV. 1850, are hereby extended to all sales under Act VIII. 1835.`
  line ________
